description: After 10 days of protests, Alexander Lukashenko says he has given orders to end the unrest in Minsk.
title: Belarus unrest: Lukashenko steps up efforts to reassert control
title_page: Belarus unrest: Lukashenko steps up efforts to reassert control - BBC News
maintext: He also warned that workers at state media who had gone on strike in protest at the election and the subsequent crackdown on protests that they would not get their jobs back. Russian replacements have reportedly been brought in. Mr Lukashenko also accused those picketing outside factories of harassing workers.
